<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Inline non-replaced elements with auto margins</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Computed value of 'auto' for 'margin-left' and 'margin-right' becomes a used value of '0'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #span1
            {
                margin-left: 0;
                margin-right: 0;
                background: red;
            }
            #span2
            {
                margin-left: auto;
                margin-right: auto;
                background: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is red is visible on the page.</p>
        <div>
            <span id="span1"><span id="span2">Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text </span></span>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>